## How the Routing Works — Very Simple

The `application.yml` has these rules:

```
If URL is  /api/items/**        → send to item-service
If URL is  /api/inventory/**    → send to inventory-service
If URL is  /api/notifications/** → send to notification-service
If URL is  /api/audit-logs/**   → send to audit-service
```

The `lb://item-service` means — look up item-service address from Eureka. This is why Eureka and Gateway work together perfectly.

